Social distancing is a luxury you don’t have aboard a nuclear-powered aircraft carrier.
So a word about Thursday’s firing of a Navy officer who showed up in the news asking for help containing a coronavirus outbreak on his ship, the USS Theodore Roosevelt.
Many have been quick to lionize Capt.
Brett Crozier as a hero who spoke up in defense of his crew.
His March 30 four-page letter, which leaked to the press this week, said he urgently needed to offload some 4,000 deployed sailors to quarantine in Guam to arrest the virus....